{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782919184809,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"id":"prt_f1e43c1a5001RNy9LY6arX8Lzg","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1782919212113,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"id":"prt_f1e43eea50018LrqlRZi312wgF","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","type":"text","text":"The TOML mirror cluster is also confirmed: multiple live skill docs require `.opencode/agents/*.toml`, but the current workspace has zero matching files and the audit spec records that this mirror requirement was removed as obsolete.","time":{"start":1782919196326,"end":1782919212104},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d3c9212932879e4016a45301c4f088191be92257d7e8e2093","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212520,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_7679NnlthYPPWb5ayfOpXOUx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"\\.opencode/agents/\\{name\\}\\.toml|agents/\\$\\{name\\}\\.toml|\\.toml","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts","include":"*.cjs"},"output":"Found 2 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs:\n  Line 18:   '.opencode/agents/{name}.toml',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/promote-candidate.cjs:\n  Line 297:     || /^(\\.\\/)?\\.opencode\\/agents\\/[^/]+\\.toml$/.test(normalized);\n","metadata":{"matches":2,"truncated":false},"title":"\\.opencode/agents/\\{name\\}\\.toml|agents/\\$\\{name\\}\\.toml|\\.toml","time":{"start":1782919212477,"end":1782919212512}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c091881918a335e7e003d4198"}},"id":"prt_f1e442c50001RggP1pbdIZ1YUl","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212520,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BxBe6sjB5tQlgVKrIcokWeQl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md","offset":1,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Integration Scanning\n3: description: How the integration scanner discovers all surfaces an agent touches across the repo.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"integration scanning\"\n6:   - \"agent integration surfaces\"\n7:   - \"mirror drift detection\"\n8:   - \"integration scan report\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.17.0.23\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Integration Scanning\n15: \n16: How `scan-integration.cjs` discovers the full integration surface of any agent across the repository.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Provides a complete inventory of every file and surface that references or depends on a given agent, so the evaluator can measure integration consistency rather than just prompt-file quality.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: Use this reference when:\n29: - Setting up a new agent as an evaluation target\n30: - Understanding why the integration dimension scored low\n31: - Debugging mirror drift or missing command references\n32: - Onboarding a new agent into the deep-improvement loop\n33: \n34: ### Core Principle\n35: \n36: An agent is not just its `.md` file. It exists across canonical, mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills, and global docs. Improving one surface while others drift is not real improvement.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 2. SCANNED SURFACES\n41: \n42: | Surface | Location Pattern | What It Checks |\n43: | --- | --- | --- |\n44: | Canonical | `.opencode/agents/{name}.md` | Exists, frontmatter parsed |\n45: | Claude mirror | `.claude/agents/{name}.md` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n46: | OpenCode mirror | `.opencode/agents/{name}.toml` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n47: | Commands | `.opencode/commands/**/*.md` | Files containing `@{name}` dispatch |\n48: | YAML workflows | `.opencode/commands/**/assets/*.yaml` | Files referencing `@{name}` |\n49: | Skills | `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` | Files referencing the agent |\n50: | Global docs | `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/CLAUDE.md` | Agent name references |\n51: | Skill advisor | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | Routing entries |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. MIRROR SYNC DETECTION\n56: \n57: Mirror sync is determined by signal matching, not byte-identical comparison:\n58: \n59: 1. Strip frontmatter from both canonical and mirror\n60: 2. Extract 3 key signal strings from the canonical body (first 3 emphasized lines over 20 characters)\n61: 3. Count how many signals appear in the mirror body\n62: 4. 2/3 or 3/3 matches = `aligned`, 0/3 or 1/3 = `diverged`, file missing = `missing`\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## 4. USAGE\n67: \n68: ```bash\n69: node scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent={agent-name} [--repo-root=.] [--output=path.json]\n70: ```\n71: \n72: The output JSON includes a `summary` with `totalSurfaces`, `existingCount`, `missingCount`, `mirrorSyncStatus`, `commandCount`, and `skillCount`.\n73: \n74: ### Example Output\n75: \n76: ```json\n77: {\n78:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n79:   \"agent\": \"{agent-name}\",\n80:   \"surfaces\": {\n81:     \"canonical\": { \"path\": \".opencode/agents/{agent-name}.md\", \"exists\": true },\n82:     \"mirrors\": [\n83:       { \"path\": \".claude/agents/{agent-name}.md\", \"syncStatus\": \"aligned\" },\n84:       { \"path\": \".opencode/agents/{agent-name}.toml\", \"syncStatus\": \"aligned\" }\n85:     ],\n86:     \"commands\": [{ \"path\": \".opencode/commands/speckit/{agent-name}.md\", \"references\": [\"@{agent-name}\"] }],\n87:     \"skills\": [{ \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/SKILL.md\", \"referenceCount\": 2 }]\n88:   },\n89:   \"summary\": {\n90:     \"totalSurfaces\": 27,\n91:     \"existingCount\": 27,\n92:     \"mirrorSyncStatus\": \"all-aligned\",\n93:     \"commandCount\": 5,\n94:     \"skillCount\": 3\n95:   }\n96: }\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 105. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Integration Scanning\ndescription: How the integration scanner discovers all surfaces an agent touches across the repo.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"integration scanning\"\n  - \"agent integration surfaces\"\n  - \"mirror drift detection\"\n  - \"integration scan report\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.17.0.23\n---\n\n# Integration Scanning\n\nHow `scan-integration.cjs` discovers the full integration surface of any agent across the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md","text":"---\ntitle: Integration Scanning\ndescription: How the integration scanner discovers all surfaces an agent touches across the repo.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"integration scanning\"\n  - \"agent integration surfaces\"\n  - \"mirror drift detection\"\n  - \"integration scan report\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.17.0.23\n---\n\n# Integration Scanning\n\nHow `scan-integration.cjs` discovers the full integration surface of any agent across the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a complete inventory of every file and surface that references or depends on a given agent, so the evaluator can measure integration consistency rather than just prompt-file quality.\n\n### When to Use\n\nUse this reference when:\n- Setting up a new agent as an evaluation target\n- Understanding why the integration dimension scored low\n- Debugging mirror drift or missing command references\n- Onboarding a new agent into the deep-improvement loop\n\n### Core Principle\n\nAn agent is not just its `.md` file. It exists across canonical, mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills, and global docs. Improving one surface while others drift is not real improvement.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCANNED SURFACES\n\n| Surface | Location Pattern | What It Checks |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Canonical | `.opencode/agents/{name}.md` | Exists, frontmatter parsed |\n| Claude mirror | `.claude/agents/{name}.md` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n| OpenCode mirror | `.opencode/agents/{name}.toml` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n| Commands | `.opencode/commands/**/*.md` | Files containing `@{name}` dispatch |\n| YAML workflows | `.opencode/commands/**/assets/*.yaml` | Files referencing `@{name}` |\n| Skills | `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` | Files referencing the agent |\n| Global docs | `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/CLAUDE.md` | Agent name references |\n| Skill advisor | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | Routing entries |\n\n---\n\n## 3. MIRROR SYNC DETECTION\n\nMirror sync is determined by signal matching, not byte-identical comparison:\n\n1. Strip frontmatter from both canonical and mirror\n2. Extract 3 key signal strings from the canonical body (first 3 emphasized lines over 20 characters)\n3. Count how many signals appear in the mirror body\n4. 2/3 or 3/3 matches = `aligned`, 0/3 or 1/3 = `diverged`, file missing = `missing`\n\n---\n\n## 4. USAGE\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent={agent-name} [--repo-root=.] [--output=path.json]\n```\n\nThe output JSON includes a `summary` with `totalSurfaces`, `existingCount`, `missingCount`, `mirrorSyncStatus`, `commandCount`, and `skillCount`.\n\n### Example Output\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"agent\": \"{agent-name}\",\n  \"surfaces\": {\n    \"canonical\": { \"path\": \".opencode/agents/{agent-name}.md\", \"exists\": true },\n    \"mirrors\": [\n      { \"path\": \".claude/agents/{agent-name}.md\", \"syncStatus\": \"aligned\" },\n      { \"path\": \".opencode/agents/{agent-name}.toml\", \"syncStatus\": \"aligned\" }\n    ],\n    \"commands\": [{ \"path\": \".opencode/commands/speckit/{agent-name}.md\", \"references\": [\"@{agent-name}\"] }],\n    \"skills\": [{ \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/SKILL.md\", \"referenceCount\": 2 }]\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"totalSurfaces\": 27,\n    \"existingCount\": 27,\n    \"mirrorSyncStatus\": \"all-aligned\",\n    \"commandCount\": 5,\n    \"skillCount\": 3\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":100,"totalLines":105,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md","time":{"start":1782919212494,"end":1782919212516}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c092881918ed8c035e38ffeb6"}},"id":"prt_f1e442dc0001kYtKt0ZSfkVica","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212520,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_luXWM3xESCxytLtA1PzoDECg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/mirror_drift_policy.md","offset":1,"limit":95},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/mirror_drift_policy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Mirror Drift Policy\n3: description: Policy for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical deep-improvement promotion.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"mirror drift policy\"\n6:   - \"runtime mirror sync\"\n7:   - \"agent definition drift\"\n8:   - \"packaging parity after promotion\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.17.0.13\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Mirror Drift Policy\n15: \n16: Policy reference for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical mutation. Use it when packaging parity must be reviewed without confusing mirror-sync work with evaluator truth.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Defines how runtime-mirror drift should be reviewed and recorded after a canonical target changes.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: Use this reference when:\n29: - a canonical promotion has happened\n30: - runtime mirrors may now be stale\n31: - packaging parity work must be captured honestly\n32: \n33: ### Core Principle\n34: \n35: Mirror drift is real maintenance work, but it is downstream from experiment truth and must not be mistaken for benchmark evidence.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. POLICY\n40: \n41: Runtime mirrors are not phase-one experiment targets. They are downstream packaging surfaces.\n42: \n43: For guarded promotion of agent definitions, downstream does not mean optional. Before an agent-definition candidate can be promoted, `.opencode/agents/`, `.claude/agents/`, and `.opencode/agents/` must all contain the corresponding agent and must match the proposed body. OpenCode TOML is compared by its extracted `developer_instructions` body tokens so runtime wrapper metadata does not create false drift.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 3. AFTER CANONICAL CHANGE\n48: \n49: After a canonical promotion:\n50: \n51: 1. Run a drift review against `.claude/agents/` and `.opencode/agents/`\n52: 2. Record the sync work under a packaging-specific note or follow-up packet\n53: 3. Decide whether to sync immediately or record explicit follow-up debt\n54: 4. Do not treat mirror changes as evaluator evidence for the original experiment\n55: \n56: If a resume detects `mirror_sync_state: \"partial:<runtime-list>\"`, the default recovery is rollback of partial mirror landings before further promotion work. Operators may override that default only by choosing to retry failed mirrors or by recording an explicit operator decision. `verification_failed` means the verifier could not establish a safe runtime set and must be treated as a stop condition.\n57: \n58: ### Integration Scanner\n59: \n60: Use `scan-integration.cjs` as the primary tool for detecting mirror drift. It replaces manual file-by-file comparison with automated signal-matching across all 3 runtime mirrors:\n61: \n62: ```text\n63: node scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent={agent-name}\n64: ```\n65: \n66: The scanner reports `aligned`, `diverged`, or `missing` for each mirror surface based on signal string matching against the canonical body.\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 4. ALLOWED AND FORBIDDEN OUTCOMES\n71: \n72: Allowed outcomes:\n73: - immediate sync for packaging parity\n74: - drift report plus follow-up packet\n75: - packaging-only verification logs outside the benchmark ledger\n76: \n77: Forbidden outcomes:\n78: - quietly leaving mirror drift undocumented\n79: - counting a mirror-sync success as proof that the canonical benchmark improved\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n84: \n85: - `../shared/rollback_runbook.md`\n86: - `../shared/promotion_rules.md`\n87: - `../../scripts/agent-improvement/check-mirror-drift.cjs`\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Mirror Drift Policy\ndescription: Policy for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical deep-improvement promotion.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mirror drift policy\"\n  - \"runtime mirror sync\"\n  - \"agent definition drift\"\n  - \"packaging parity after promotion\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.17.0.13\n---\n\n# Mirror Drift Policy\n\nPolicy reference for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical mutation. Use it when packaging parity must be reviewed without confusing mirror-sync work with evaluator truth.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/mirror_drift_policy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Mirror Drift Policy\ndescription: Policy for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical deep-improvement promotion.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mirror drift policy\"\n  - \"runtime mirror sync\"\n  - \"agent definition drift\"\n  - \"packaging parity after promotion\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.17.0.13\n---\n\n# Mirror Drift Policy\n\nPolicy reference for handling runtime mirror drift after canonical mutation. Use it when packaging parity must be reviewed without confusing mirror-sync work with evaluator truth.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefines how runtime-mirror drift should be reviewed and recorded after a canonical target changes.\n\n### When to Use\n\nUse this reference when:\n- a canonical promotion has happened\n- runtime mirrors may now be stale\n- packaging parity work must be captured honestly\n\n### Core Principle\n\nMirror drift is real maintenance work, but it is downstream from experiment truth and must not be mistaken for benchmark evidence.\n\n---\n\n## 2. POLICY\n\nRuntime mirrors are not phase-one experiment targets. They are downstream packaging surfaces.\n\nFor guarded promotion of agent definitions, downstream does not mean optional. Before an agent-definition candidate can be promoted, `.opencode/agents/`, `.claude/agents/`, and `.opencode/agents/` must all contain the corresponding agent and must match the proposed body. OpenCode TOML is compared by its extracted `developer_instructions` body tokens so runtime wrapper metadata does not create false drift.\n\n---\n\n## 3. AFTER CANONICAL CHANGE\n\nAfter a canonical promotion:\n\n1. Run a drift review against `.claude/agents/` and `.opencode/agents/`\n2. Record the sync work under a packaging-specific note or follow-up packet\n3. Decide whether to sync immediately or record explicit follow-up debt\n4. Do not treat mirror changes as evaluator evidence for the original experiment\n\nIf a resume detects `mirror_sync_state: \"partial:<runtime-list>\"`, the default recovery is rollback of partial mirror landings before further promotion work. Operators may override that default only by choosing to retry failed mirrors or by recording an explicit operator decision. `verification_failed` means the verifier could not establish a safe runtime set and must be treated as a stop condition.\n\n### Integration Scanner\n\nUse `scan-integration.cjs` as the primary tool for detecting mirror drift. It replaces manual file-by-file comparison with automated signal-matching across all 3 runtime mirrors:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent={agent-name}\n```\n\nThe scanner reports `aligned`, `diverged`, or `missing` for each mirror surface based on signal string matching against the canonical body.\n\n---\n\n## 4. ALLOWED AND FORBIDDEN OUTCOMES\n\nAllowed outcomes:\n- immediate sync for packaging parity\n- drift report plus follow-up packet\n- packaging-only verification logs outside the benchmark ledger\n\nForbidden outcomes:\n- quietly leaving mirror drift undocumented\n- counting a mirror-sync success as proof that the canonical benchmark improved\n\n---\n\n## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `../shared/rollback_runbook.md`\n- `../shared/promotion_rules.md`\n- `../../scripts/agent-improvement/check-mirror-drift.cjs`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":87,"totalLines":87,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/mirror_drift_policy.md","time":{"start":1782919212505,"end":1782919212518}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c0930819180902be980c059af"}},"id":"prt_f1e442dd6001oeKvyq0uBXnxIt","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212520,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JG0MkSGiqWj27Pc0oMzwY052","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md","offset":70,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n70: `-- README.md\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 4. KEY FILES\n76: \n77: | File | Responsibility |\n78: |---|---|\n79: | `score-candidate.cjs` | Lane entrypoint. Reads candidate (and optional baseline), spawns `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs`, scores structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, and systemFitness dimensions, applies weights and promotion gates, caches by input hash, and emits a `scored` result with `mode: 'agent-improvement'`. |\n80: | `generate-profile.cjs` | Parses an agent file into a profile with `derivedChecks` (structural sections, rule coherence, output checks, anti-patterns, integration points, capability mismatches). CLI: `--agent=<path>` with optional `--output` and `--state-dir`. |\n81: | `scan-integration.cjs` | Scans the three runtime mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills, global docs, and the skill advisor for an agent name. CLI: `--agent=<name>` with optional `--repo-root` and `--output`. Emits `status: 'complete'` with `surfaces` and `summary`. |\n82: | `candidate-lineage.cjs` | Library exports (`createLineageGraph`, `recordCandidate`, `getLineage`, `getChildren`, and related) tracking candidate derivation across parallel waves by content hash. |\n83: | `trade-off-detector.cjs` | Library exports (`detectTradeOffs`, `getTrajectory`, `checkParetoDominance`) flagging cross-dimension regressions using hard and soft dimension thresholds. |\n84: | `benchmark-stability.cjs` | Library exports (`measureStability`, `stabilityCoefficient`, `generateWeightRecommendations`, and related) reporting score variance and weight-optimization advisories. |\n85: | `check-mirror-drift.cjs` | CLI reporting drift between a canonical agent body and its mirrors. Args include `--output`, `--canonical`, `--mirrors`, `--manifest`. |\n86: | `rollback-candidate.cjs` | CLI restoring the single canonical manifest target from a backup. Args include `--target`, `--backup`, `--config`, `--manifest`. |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 5. BOUNDARIES AND FLOW\n91: \n92: | Boundary | Rule |\n93: |---|---|\n94: | Imports | May import `../lib/*` (`typed-errors.cjs`, `promotion-gates.cjs`). `score-candidate.cjs` spawns sibling `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs` as child processes. |\n\n(Showing lines 70-94 of 166. Use offset=95 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"`-- README.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. KEY FILES\n\n| File | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `score-candidate.cjs` | Lane entrypoint. Reads candidate (and optional baseline), spawns `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs`, scores structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, and systemFitness dimensions, applies weights and promotion gates, caches by input hash, and emits a `scored` result with `mode: 'agent-improvement'`. |\n| `generate-profile.cjs` | Parses an agent file into a profile with `derivedChecks` (structural sections, rule coherence, output checks, anti-patterns, integration points, capability mismatches). CLI: `--agent=<path>` with optional `--output` and `--state-dir`. |\n| `scan-integration.cjs` | Scans the three runtime mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills, global docs, and the skill advisor for an agent name. CLI: `--agent=<name>` with optional `--repo-root` and `--output`. Emits `status: 'complete'` with `surfaces` and `summary`. |\n| `candidate-lineage.cjs` | Library exports (`createLineageGraph`, `recordCandidate`, `getLineage`, `getChildren`, and related) tracking candidate derivation across parallel waves by content hash. |\n| `trade-off-detector.cjs` | Library exports (`detectTradeOffs`, `getTrajectory`, `checkParetoDominance`) flagging cross-dimension regressions using hard and soft dimension thresholds. |\n| `benchmark-stability.cjs` | Library exports (`measureStability`, `stabilityCoefficient`, `generateWeightRecommendations`, and related) reporting score variance and weight-optimization advisories. |\n| `check-mirror-drift.cjs` | CLI reporting drift between a canonical agent body and its mirrors. Args include `--output`, `--canonical`, `--mirrors`, `--manifest`. |\n| `rollback-candidate.cjs` | CLI restoring the single canonical manifest target from a backup. Args include `--target`, `--backup`, `--config`, `--manifest`. |\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md","text":"`-- README.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. KEY FILES\n\n| File | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `score-candidate.cjs` | Lane entrypoint. Reads candidate (and optional baseline), spawns `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs`, scores structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, and systemFitness dimensions, applies weights and promotion gates, caches by input hash, and emits a `scored` result with `mode: 'agent-improvement'`. |\n| `generate-profile.cjs` | Parses an agent file into a profile with `derivedChecks` (structural sections, rule coherence, output checks, anti-patterns, integration points, capability mismatches). CLI: `--agent=<path>` with optional `--output` and `--state-dir`. |\n| `scan-integration.cjs` | Scans the three runtime mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills, global docs, and the skill advisor for an agent name. CLI: `--agent=<name>` with optional `--repo-root` and `--output`. Emits `status: 'complete'` with `surfaces` and `summary`. |\n| `candidate-lineage.cjs` | Library exports (`createLineageGraph`, `recordCandidate`, `getLineage`, `getChildren`, and related) tracking candidate derivation across parallel waves by content hash. |\n| `trade-off-detector.cjs` | Library exports (`detectTradeOffs`, `getTrajectory`, `checkParetoDominance`) flagging cross-dimension regressions using hard and soft dimension thresholds. |\n| `benchmark-stability.cjs` | Library exports (`measureStability`, `stabilityCoefficient`, `generateWeightRecommendations`, and related) reporting score variance and weight-optimization advisories. |\n| `check-mirror-drift.cjs` | CLI reporting drift between a canonical agent body and its mirrors. Args include `--output`, `--canonical`, `--mirrors`, `--manifest`. |\n| `rollback-candidate.cjs` | CLI restoring the single canonical manifest target from a backup. Args include `--target`, `--backup`, `--config`, `--manifest`. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. BOUNDARIES AND FLOW\n\n| Boundary | Rule |\n|---|---|\n| Imports | May import `../lib/*` (`typed-errors.cjs`, `promotion-gates.cjs`). `score-candidate.cjs` spawns sibling `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs` as child processes. |","lineStart":70,"lineEnd":94,"totalLines":166,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md","time":{"start":1782919212507,"end":1782919212519}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c0938819189fd84c4344ce12e"}},"id":"prt_f1e442dd9001A3R847iq1TOwDE","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212527,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_nmzgYNp2jY75O8jhbGn9hpPV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md","offset":1,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Surface discovery\"\n3: description: \"Discovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"surface discovery\"\n6:   - \"scan-integration.cjs\"\n7:   - \"discover agent surfaces\"\n8:   - \"repo surface inventory\"\n9:   - \"integration surface scan\"\n10: version: 1.17.0.12\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Surface discovery\n14: \n15: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: Discovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\n20: \n21: This feature covers the repository scan that feeds integration consistency scoring and gives operators a concrete list of what would drift if the canonical agent changed.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n26: \n27: `scan-integration.cjs` inventories the canonical `.opencode/agents/{name}.md` file, runtime mirrors, improve-command markdown, YAML workflow assets, skill references, global docs, and one skill-advisor lookup. Command markdown is scanned for `@{agent}` dispatch, while YAML is scanned for either `@{agent}` or bare agent-name references.\n28: \n29: The discovery map includes the consolidated advisor script at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`, so the skill-advisor surface is registered from its self-contained package location.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n34: \n35: ### Implementation\n36: \n37: | File | Layer | Role |\n38: |---|---|---|\n39: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs` | Scanner | Walks the repo and collects canonical, mirror, command, YAML, skill, global-doc, and skill-advisor surfaces. |\n40: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md` | Reference | Documents the intended scan taxonomy and output summary fields. |\n41: | `.opencode/commands/deep/agent-improvement.md` | Command | Uses the integration report as part of loop setup and review. |\n42: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs` | Scoring consumer | Converts the scan results into the integration dimension score. |\n43: \n44: ### Validation And Tests\n45: \n46: | File | Type | Role |\n47: |---|---|---|\n48: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/model_benchmark/evaluator_contract.md` | Contract reference | Locks the scanner into the integration-consistency dimension and its weighted contribution. |\n49: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/target_onboarding.md` | Operator reference | Requires the integration scan before new targets enter the loop. |\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n54: \n55: - Group: Integration scanning\n56: - Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n57: - Feature file path: `02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md`\n58: Related references:\n59: - [runtime-mirrors.md](runtime-mirrors.md) — Runtime mirrors\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Surface discovery\"\ndescription: \"Discovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"surface discovery\"\n  - \"scan-integration.cjs\"\n  - \"discover agent surfaces\"\n  - \"repo surface inventory\"\n  - \"integration surface scan\"\nversion: 1.17.0.12\n---\n\n# Surface discovery\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDiscovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Surface discovery\"\ndescription: \"Discovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"surface discovery\"\n  - \"scan-integration.cjs\"\n  - \"discover agent surfaces\"\n  - \"repo surface inventory\"\n  - \"integration surface scan\"\nversion: 1.17.0.12\n---\n\n# Surface discovery\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDiscovers the repo surfaces that define an agent beyond its canonical markdown file.\n\nThis feature covers the repository scan that feeds integration consistency scoring and gives operators a concrete list of what would drift if the canonical agent changed.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\n`scan-integration.cjs` inventories the canonical `.opencode/agents/{name}.md` file, runtime mirrors, improve-command markdown, YAML workflow assets, skill references, global docs, and one skill-advisor lookup. Command markdown is scanned for `@{agent}` dispatch, while YAML is scanned for either `@{agent}` or bare agent-name references.\n\nThe discovery map includes the consolidated advisor script at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`, so the skill-advisor surface is registered from its self-contained package location.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Layer | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs` | Scanner | Walks the repo and collects canonical, mirror, command, YAML, skill, global-doc, and skill-advisor surfaces. |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md` | Reference | Documents the intended scan taxonomy and output summary fields. |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/agent-improvement.md` | Command | Uses the integration report as part of loop setup and review. |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs` | Scoring consumer | Converts the scan results into the integration dimension score. |\n\n### Validation And Tests\n\n| File | Type | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/model_benchmark/evaluator_contract.md` | Contract reference | Locks the scanner into the integration-consistency dimension and its weighted contribution. |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/target_onboarding.md` | Operator reference | Requires the integration scan before new targets enter the loop. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: Integration scanning\n- Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n- Feature file path: `02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md`\nRelated references:\n- [runtime-mirrors.md](runtime-mirrors.md) — Runtime mirrors","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":59,"totalLines":59,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/surface-discovery.md","time":{"start":1782919212514,"end":1782919212526}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c09408191b34d3cced0550b5e"}},"id":"prt_f1e442ddc001rlSz7lAUvUaRla","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919212550,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jmr4rVFUuMjkR2FRPV5aHM3k","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/shared/promotion_rules.md","offset":84,"limit":18},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/shared/promotion_rules.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n84: \n85: ## 5. PROMOTION PREREQUISITES\n86: \n87: Promotion is allowed only when:\n88: - artifact-level fixtures exist (or are waived for the specific target)\n89: - repeatability is proven for the active benchmark set\n90: - rollback steps are documented\n91: - accept/ship evidence is present when using the two-phase path\n92: - the explicit approval gate is passed\n93: - the target is not classified `fixed` or `forbidden` in the manifest\n94: - agent-definition targets are present and content-aligned across all four runtime mirrors; OpenCode TOML is checked by extracted body tokens, not by byte-equivalence of the TOML wrapper\n95: \n96: If mirror verification fails, promotion rejects with a structured `MIRROR_SYNC_GATE_FAILED` error. The optional promotion state file records `mirror_sync_state` as `all_landed`, `partial:<runtime-list>`, or `verification_failed`. Resume behavior defaults to rolling back partial mirror landings before another promotion attempt; operators may instead retry failed mirrors or pause for an explicit decision.\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## 6. NO-GO CONDITIONS\n101: \n\n(Showing lines 84-101 of 126. Use offset=102 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n## 5. PROMOTION PREREQUISITES\n\nPromotion is allowed only when:\n- artifact-level fixtures exist (or are waived for the specific target)\n- repeatability is proven for the active benchmark set\n- rollback steps are documented\n- accept/ship evidence is present when using the two-phase path\n- the explicit approval gate is passed\n- the target is not classified `fixed` or `forbidden` in the manifest\n- agent-definition targets are present and content-aligned across all four runtime mirrors; OpenCode TOML is checked by extracted body tokens, not by byte-equivalence of the TOML wrapper\n\nIf mirror verification fails, promotion rejects with a structured `MIRROR_SYNC_GATE_FAILED` error. The optional promotion state file records `mirror_sync_state` as `all_landed`, `partial:<runtime-list>`, or `verification_failed`. Resume behavior defaults to rolling back partial mirror landings before another promotion attempt; operators may instead retry failed mirrors or pause for an explicit decision.\n\n---\n\n## 6. NO-GO CONDITIONS\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/shared/promotion_rules.md","text":"\n## 5. PROMOTION PREREQUISITES\n\nPromotion is allowed only when:\n- artifact-level fixtures exist (or are waived for the specific target)\n- repeatability is proven for the active benchmark set\n- rollback steps are documented\n- accept/ship evidence is present when using the two-phase path\n- the explicit approval gate is passed\n- the target is not classified `fixed` or `forbidden` in the manifest\n- agent-definition targets are present and content-aligned across all four runtime mirrors; OpenCode TOML is checked by extracted body tokens, not by byte-equivalence of the TOML wrapper\n\nIf mirror verification fails, promotion rejects with a structured `MIRROR_SYNC_GATE_FAILED` error. The optional promotion state file records `mirror_sync_state` as `all_landed`, `partial:<runtime-list>`, or `verification_failed`. Resume behavior defaults to rolling back partial mirror landings before another promotion attempt; operators may instead retry failed mirrors or pause for an explicit decision.\n\n---\n\n## 6. NO-GO CONDITIONS\n","lineStart":84,"lineEnd":101,"totalLines":126,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/shared/promotion_rules.md","time":{"start":1782919212546,"end":1782919212549}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3c9212932879e4016a45302c094481919bc7a35cdacf0f6a"}},"id":"prt_f1e442e01001BvzWffzbBO6g9b","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e43adea001rzFMxU4O3J6nCO"}}
