{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919293329,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_MRcsCOlNkw3ahMf0lTjQWsvP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"ai-council|mode: all|mode: subagent|--agent ai-council|\\.opencode/agents/.*toml|runtime mirrors|deep-route-guard|mk-deep-loop-guard|orchestrate|Deep Route","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md","include":"SKILL.md"},"output":"Found 49 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md:\n  Line 38: - Strategy deliberation between competing plans — use `deep-ai-council`.\n\n  Line 279: The native `@deep-context` seat is dispatched **by name** (`agent: deep-context` in the loop YAML), resolved by each host runtime from its OWN `agents/` directory. It therefore lives as one canonical source plus two runtime mirrors that must stay in sync:\n\n  Line 283: | OpenCode | `.opencode/agents/deep-context.md` | **canonical source** — `mode: subagent` + `permission:` block |\n\n  Line 285: | OpenCode | `.opencode/agents/deep-context.toml` | mirror — `developer_instructions = '''…'''` + `# Converted from:` header + `sandbox_mode = \"read-only\"`, same body |\n\n  Line 302: 8. **Keep the native agent's runtime mirrors in sync** — when editing `.opencode/agents/deep-context.md` (canonical), update `.claude/agents/deep-context.md` and `.opencode/agents/deep-context.toml` in the same change. The loop dispatches the native seat by name from each runtime's own `agents/` dir, so a missing mirror means native seats silently fail to dispatch in that runtime. See **Runtime Mirrors** in §3.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:\n  Line 4: description: \"Unified deep-loop workflow skill: routes a request to one of five modes (context, research, review, ai-council, improvement) over the shared deep-loop-runtime backend. Holds no per-mode logic — it dispatches by workflowMode through mode-registry.json. Use for codebase-context gathering, autonomous research, iterative code review, multi-seat AI Council planning, and evaluator-first agent/model/skill/non-dev-system improvement.\"\n\n  Line 8: <!-- Keywords: deep-loop-workflows, deep-loop, deep-context, deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement, context-gathering, reuse-catalog, autoresearch, iterative-research, code-audit, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, ai-council, council-deliberation, multi-seat-planning, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, model-benchmark, skill-benchmark, non-dev-ai-system, convergence-detection, externalized-state, coverage-graph, mode-registry, workflowmode, runtimeloop-type, backendkind -->\n\n  Line 25: | **ai-council** | Multi-seat planning deliberation → `ai-council/**` artifacts | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/` | `/deep:ai-council` | `ai-council` |\n\n  Line 39: - **`workflowMode`** — the public mode key (all modes): `context`, `research`, `review`, `ai-council`, and the four improvement lanes `agent-improvement`, `model-benchmark`, `skill-benchmark`, `ai-system-improvement` (its loop-host mode stays `non-dev-ai-system-refine`).\n\n  Line 40: - **`runtimeLoopType`** — the graph-backed convergence key consumed by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` (validated against exactly `research|review|council|context`). **Explicit `null` for all four improvement lanes; never inferred from `workflowMode`.** Note `ai-council` maps to `runtimeLoopType: council`.\n\n  Line 41: - **`backendKind`** — which backend runs the mode: `runtime-loop-type` (context/research/review/ai-council), `improvement-host` (`deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode`), or `external-adapter` (non-dev-ai-system; the loop is owned by external packaging).\n\n  Line 55: Intent classification favors the single dominant deep-loop mode; a mode hint (`research: ...`, `review: ...`, `context: ...`, `ai-council: ...`, or an improvement lane) overrides the classifier. The legacy advisor projection maps stay hardcoded and drift-guarded against the registry, and the command files remain static routers with hardcoded asset/mode routing; neither resolves from `mode-registry.json` at runtime, but both stay equal to its projection.\n\n  Line 57: Per-mode behavior is **not flattened**: each packet keeps its own convergence math, state shape, artifacts, and tool-permission guards (research has WebFetch; review/context/ai-council are code/inward-only; improvement is the only mutating family). Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` — this hub's — is preserved, so the advisor discovers exactly one skill identity regardless of which surface (hub `Skill()`, `/deep:*` command, or agent) reaches a mode.\n\n  Line 69:   deep-context/   deep-research/   deep-review/   deep-ai-council/   deep-improvement/   # five verbatim mode packets\n\n  Line 73: Each mode packet is the former skill's content moved verbatim (its own `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `scripts/`, `assets/`, `feature_catalog/`, `manual_testing_playbook/`), with internal paths repointed and **no per-packet `graph-metadata.json`** — only this hub carries one, so the advisor discovers exactly one skill. The `deep-ai-council` packet folder follows the standard `folder == packetSkillName` convention (`deep-ai-council`); its legacy public surfaces (the `/deep:ai-council` command and the `ai-council` agent) intentionally keep the shorter `ai-council` key, so always resolve the packet path through `mode-registry.json` rather than hardcoding it.\n\n  Line 92: - **NEVER** let a read-only mode (context/research/review/ai-council) reach the improvement mutation scripts (`promote-candidate.cjs`/`rollback-candidate.cjs`).\n\n  Line 104: - Mode packets: `deep-context/SKILL.md`, `deep-research/SKILL.md`, `deep-review/SKILL.md`, `deep-ai-council/SKILL.md`, `deep-improvement/SKILL.md` (per-mode detail).\n\n  Line 125: - `ai-council` — multi-seat planning deliberation (`ai-council/**` artifacts).\n\n  Line 129: - `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` is the invokable hub; the `/deep:*` commands and the agent types (`deep-context`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `ai-council`, `deep-improvement`) are complementary surfaces over the same packets.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md:\n  Line 20: - OpenCode runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.toml`\n\n  Line 35: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\n  Line 439: Cross-skill alignment: `deep-research` owns iterative investigation. Its shared resource family mirrors `deep-review` and `deep-ai-council`, but its vocabulary remains novelty, sources, negative knowledge, question coverage, and research synthesis rather than severity findings or council agreement.\n\n  Line 476: - **Orchestrator**: @orchestrate dispatches @deep-research as LEAF agent\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:\n  Line 2: name: deep-ai-council\n\n  Line 3: description: \"AI Council: multi-seat planning, artifact persistence, convergence checks, packet-local ai-council outputs.\"\n\n  Line 8: <!-- Keywords: deep-ai-council, ai council, council deliberation, multi-seat planning, ai-council artifacts, council convergence, planning council, council artifact persistence -->\n\n  Line 12: Planning-only council deliberation with diverse seats, convergence checks, and packet-local `ai-council/**` artifact persistence.\n\n  Line 69: - Treating council graph rows as source-of-truth or replacing packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts.\n\n  Line 75: - deep-ai-council\n\n  Line 83: - packet-local ai-council\n\n  Line 95:   *\"persist council\"*|*\"ai-council artifact\"*|*\"council_complete\"*) COUNCIL_INTENT=1 ;;\n\n  Line 126: - `scripts/` contains deterministic helpers; scripts are invoked explicitly and are not markdown-routed. Notable entries: `persist-artifacts.cjs` (artifact writer CLI), `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` (DAC-025 derived-projection rebuild — reads `ai-council-state.jsonl` and writes through `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council`, with `--dry-run` for payload inspection).\n\n  Line 148:     \"ARTIFACT_PERSISTENCE\": {\"keywords\": [(\"persist council\", 5), (\"ai-council artifact\", 5), (\"council report parser\", 4), (\"state jsonl\", 3)]},\n\n  Line 292: The skill guides planning-only council runs from packet resolution through deliberation, persistence, and handoff. It keeps council artifacts under `ai-council/**` and leaves implementation to the caller or implementation agents.\n\n  Line 327: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs <packet> --input-file <report>\n\n  Line 328: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/advise-council-completion.cjs <packet>\n\n  Line 341: 1. **ALWAYS keep council writes scoped to packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts**\n\n  Line 354:    - The graph is rebuilt from packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts and must not replace append-only council state.\n\n  Line 363: 1. **NEVER write application code, authored spec docs, or files outside `ai-council/**` as part of a council run**\n\n  Line 386: 3. **ESCALATE IF a caller still depends on the old `ai-council` runtime name and cannot be renamed**\n\n  Line 431: - ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n\n  Line 432: - ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n\n  Line 434: - ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n\n  Line 443: - **Boundary discipline**: graph rows never replace `ai-council/**` artifacts and council seats do not mutate graph storage directly.\n\n  Line 457: Run `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` before completion claims when spec docs are updated. Skill package structure is checked with `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/quick_validate.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council`.\n\n  Line 466: - `Write` and `Edit` are allowed only for the planning LEAF's packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md:\n  Line 19: - OpenCode runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.toml` when running directly in OpenCode; external OpenCode dispatch uses `cli-opencode`.\n\n  Line 21: Convergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:\n  Line 524: - Treat runtime mirrors as experiment truth in the same phase as canonical evaluation\n","metadata":{"matches":49,"truncated":false},"title":"ai-council|mode: all|mode: subagent|--agent ai-council|\\.opencode/agents/.*toml|runtime mirrors|deep-route-guard|mk-deep-loop-guard|orchestrate|Deep Route","time":{"start":1782919293283,"end":1782919293327}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0963fe6f9a3705f5016a45307aa75c81918b52e3b264deb4fa"}},"id":"prt_f1e45695f001hSCyEXd47663TN","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","mess