{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919320275,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JppgLuhkGdph63HkFQFS0S8v","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","offset":420,"limit":22},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n420: \n421: Related skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n426: \n427: ### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n428: \n429: Council alignment is complete when:\n430: \n431: - ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n432: - ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n433: - ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n434: - ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n435: - ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n436: \n437: ### Quality Targets\n438: \n439: - **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.\n440: - **Routing**: Section 3 is the only authoritative routing source.\n441: - **Reference shape**: reference filenames are snake_case and intro sections are short.\n\n(Showing lines 420-441 of 491. Use offset=442 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n\nCouncil alignment is complete when:\n\n- ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n- ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n- ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n- ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n- ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n\n### Quality Targets\n\n- **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","text":"\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for evidence-first investigation vantages and `system-spec-kit` for packet documentation, validation, resume, and memory continuity.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Council Skill Completion Checklist\n\nCouncil alignment is complete when:\n\n- ✅ Council requests route to the `deep-ai-council` advisor/packet surface (`packetSkillName` and `legacyAdvisorId` in `mode-registry.json`); `deep-ai-council` is the packet folder/SKILL.md name (folder == name), while the dispatched agent identity remains `ai-council`.\n- ✅ Runtime mirrors dispatch `@ai-council` as the primary agent identity — the three agent files (`.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, `.claude/agents/ai-council.md`, `.opencode/agents/ai-council.toml`) all declare `name: ai-council`, matching the registry `agent: ai-council` field.\n- ✅ Council references and scripts live inside this skill package.\n- ✅ Persisted artifacts and append-only state stay under packet-local `ai-council/**`.\n- ✅ Persistence helpers parse and write the existing council artifact contract while graph support remains a derived projection.\n\n### Quality Targets\n\n- **Structure**: SKILL.md follows sk-doc required section order and frontmatter.\n- **Routing**: Section 3 is the only authoritative routing source.\n- **Reference shape**: reference filenames are snake_case and intro sections are short.","lineStart":420,"lineEnd":441,"totalLines":491,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782919320260,"end":1782919320272}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f3316023a69eb36016a45309806488191816007f9623893dc"}},"id":"prt_f1e45d267001cFg6YVDd2aPCwG","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e456dfa0017IPZw6Id1Sw2B0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919320299,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Yl8XNypT2KL4JqFnZ15q22Iy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v2.1.0.0.md","offset":1,"limit":45},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v2.1.0.0.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # v2.1.0.0: Release Cleanup\n2: \n3: Date: 2026-05-24\n4: \n5: Release-cleanup pass against current sk-doc templates and HVR standards, run as packet `116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council`. The README is rewritten to a marketing-leaning HVR voice, the missing root feature catalog is authored and surgical alignment fixes close the audit findings. Smart Router (§3) stays untouched. No backward-incompatible changes.\n6: \n7: ## What Changed\n8: \n9: #### Added\n10: \n11: - `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md` root inventory: 32 per-feature capability summaries across 9 categories with links and scenario IDs, closing the missing-root-catalog gap (AF-0002).\n12: - Release-cleanup spec folder at `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council` with 4 JSON schemas and `resource-map.yaml`.\n13: \n14: #### Changed\n15: \n16: - `README.md` full rewrite per `skill_readme_template.md`: HVR-clean, marketing-leaning voice anchored at ~70% of the root README intensity, structural pattern from `system-spec-kit/README.md`.\n17: - `SKILL.md` version frontmatter `2.0.0.0` -> `2.1.0.0`.\n18: - All 32 per-feature `Canonical catalog source` back-links now point to `feature_catalog.md` instead of the playbook (AF-0006).\n19: \n20: #### Fixed\n21: \n22: - `SKILL.md` §7 playbook-coverage count corrected from \"18 scenarios across 7 categories\" to \"32 scenarios across 9 categories\" (AF-0001).\n23: - `SKILL.md` §7 removed the stale \"Phase 001 spec folder\" phase reference (AF-0004, partial).\n24: - `references/scoring_rubric.md` Integration-dimension top-score anchor reworded to \"no friction\" for HVR compliance (AF-0003).\n25: - `README.md` runtime-parity and changelog references corrected: agent mirrors now point to the actual `ai-council.*` files across three runtimes, and the changelog list reflects the current head (AF-0005, AF-0008).\n26: \n27: #### Deferred\n28: \n29: - Agent-file rename `ai-council.*` -> `deep-ai-council.*` declined by the operator: the files keep the `ai-council` name to avoid breaking live `--agent ai-council` callers.\n30: - Broader `SKILL.md` §7 extraction-era checklist reframing left as a P2 follow-on.\n\n(End of file - total 30 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# v2.1.0.0: Release Cleanup\n\nDate: 2026-05-24\n\nRelease-cleanup pass against current sk-doc templates and HVR standards, run as packet `116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council`. The README is rewritten to a marketing-leaning HVR voice, the missing root feature catalog is authored and surgical alignment fixes close the audit findings. Smart Router (§3) stays untouched. No backward-incompatible changes.\n\n## What Changed\n\n#### Added\n\n- `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md` root inventory: 32 per-feature capability summaries across 9 categories with links and scenario IDs, closing the missing-root-catalog gap (AF-0002).\n- Release-cleanup spec folder at `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council` with 4 JSON schemas and `resource-map.yaml`.\n\n#### Changed\n\n- `README.md` full rewrite per `skill_readme_template.md`: HVR-clean, marketing-leaning voice anchored at ~70% of the root README intensity, structural pattern from `system-spec-kit/README.md`.\n- `SKILL.md` version frontmatter `2.0.0.0` -> `2.1.0.0`.\n- All 32 per-feature `Canonical catalog source` back-links now point to `feature_catalog.md` instead of the playbook (AF-0006).\n\n#### Fixed","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v2.1.0.0.md","text":"# v2.1.0.0: Release Cleanup\n\nDate: 2026-05-24\n\nRelease-cleanup pass against current sk-doc templates and HVR standards, run as packet `116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council`. The README is rewritten to a marketing-leaning HVR voice, the missing root feature catalog is authored and surgical alignment fixes close the audit findings. Smart Router (§3) stays untouched. No backward-incompatible changes.\n\n## What Changed\n\n#### Added\n\n- `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md` root inventory: 32 per-feature capability summaries across 9 categories with links and scenario IDs, closing the missing-root-catalog gap (AF-0002).\n- Release-cleanup spec folder at `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/004-deep-ai-council` with 4 JSON schemas and `resource-map.yaml`.\n\n#### Changed\n\n- `README.md` full rewrite per `skill_readme_template.md`: HVR-clean, marketing-leaning voice anchored at ~70% of the root README intensity, structural pattern from `system-spec-kit/README.md`.\n- `SKILL.md` version frontmatter `2.0.0.0` -> `2.1.0.0`.\n- All 32 per-feature `Canonical catalog source` back-links now point to `feature_catalog.md` instead of the playbook (AF-0006).\n\n#### Fixed\n\n- `SKILL.md` §7 playbook-coverage count corrected from \"18 scenarios across 7 categories\" to \"32 scenarios across 9 categories\" (AF-0001).\n- `SKILL.md` §7 removed the stale \"Phase 001 spec folder\" phase reference (AF-0004, partial).\n- `references/scoring_rubric.md` Integration-dimension top-score anchor reworded to \"no friction\" for HVR compliance (AF-0003).\n- `README.md` runtime-parity and changelog references corrected: agent mirrors now point to the actual `ai-council.*` files across three runtimes, and the changelog list reflects the current head (AF-0005, AF-0008).\n\n#### Deferred\n\n- Agent-file rename `ai-council.*` -> `deep-ai-council.*` declined by the operator: the files keep the `ai-council` name to avoid breaking live `--agent ai-council` callers.\n- Broader `SKILL.md` §7 extraction-era checklist reframing left as a P2 follow-on.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":30,"totalLines":30,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v2.1.0.0.md","time":{"start":1782919320282,"end":1782919320296}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f3316023a69eb36016a4530980660819182cb67a4391b56a0"}},"id":"prt_f1e45d2c9001wmy59OglcSkZVj","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e456dfa0017IPZw6Id1Sw2B0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919320408,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MTrlNp1EgUrnnc5JUw6vWokR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","offset":20,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: \n21: Operators need one current dispatch name across runtimes so council prompts do not split between old and new identities.\n22: \n23: Operators use this feature when the real request is: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n28: \n29: The shipped surface is anchored by `deep-ai-council`. The playbook scenario `01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md` defines the operator prompt, command sequence, expected signals, evidence, and pass/fail criteria for DAC-001.\n30: \n31: Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, which the scenario identifies as the OpenCode runtime mirror. Identity note: the agent files are `ai-council.*` (the `@ai-council` identity) because v1.2.0.0 dropped the `deep-` prefix from the agent, while the skill kept the `deep-ai-council` name. The runtime mirrors route council prompts to the `deep-ai-council` skill under the `@ai-council` agent identity. Validation is anchored by `manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md`, covering the manual scenario contract.\n32: \n33: The user-visible contract is concrete: Verify active runtime mirrors use deep-ai-council. The catalog entry mirrors that contract so reviewers can move from feature inventory to the exact playbook scenario and source files without guessing.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n38: \n39: ### Implementation\n\n(Showing lines 20-39 of 62. Use offset=40 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nOperators need one current dispatch name across runtimes so council prompts do not split between old and new identities.\n\nOperators use this feature when the real request is: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\nThe shipped surface is anchored by `deep-ai-council`. The playbook scenario `01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md` defines the operator prompt, command sequence, expected signals, evidence, and pass/fail criteria for DAC-001.\n\nCurrent behavior is grounded in `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, which the scenario identifies as the OpenCode runtime mirror. Identity note: the agent files are `ai-council.*` (the `@ai-council` identity) because v1.2.0.0 dropped the `deep-` prefix from the agent, while the skill kept the `deep-ai-council` name. The runtime mirrors route council prompts to the `deep-ai-council` skill under the `@ai-council` agent identity. Validation is anchored by `manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md`, covering the manual scenario contract.\n\nThe user-visible contract is concrete: Verify active runtime mirrors use deep-ai-council. The catalog entry mirrors that contract so reviewers can move from feature inventory to the exact playbook scenario and source files without guessing.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","text":"\nOperators need one current dispatch name across runtimes so council prompts do not split between old and new identities.\n\nOperators use this feature when the real request is: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\nThe shipped surface is anchored by `deep-ai-council`. The playbook scenario `01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md` defines the operator prompt, command sequence, expected signals, evidence, and pass/fail criteria for DAC-001.\n\nCurrent behavior is grounded in `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md`, which the scenario identifies as the OpenCode runtime mirror. Identity note: the agent files are `ai-council.*` (the `@ai-council` identity) because v1.2.0.0 dropped the `deep-` prefix from the agent, while the skill kept the `deep-ai-council` name. The runtime mirrors route council prompts to the `deep-ai-council` skill under the `@ai-council` agent identity. Validation is anchored by `manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md`, covering the manual scenario contract.\n\nThe user-visible contract is concrete: Verify active runtime mirrors use deep-ai-council. The catalog entry mirrors that contract so reviewers can move from feature inventory to the exact playbook scenario and source files without guessing.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":39,"totalLines":62,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","time":{"start":1782919320401,"end":1782919320406}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f3316023a69eb36016a453098066c8191be075043615e99b4"}},"id":"prt_f1e45d2ed001X8U1dQm5w3us30","sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","messageID":"msg_f1e456dfa0017IPZw6Id1Sw2B0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782919320589,"sessionID":"ses_0e1c04adcffe04QJWsDQQqIgY4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_eCG1d5edznpHHwNgpTt5BbcV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","offset":20,"limit":16},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n24: \n25: - Objective: Verify active runtime mirrors use `deep-ai-council`.\n26: - Real user request: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n27: - Prompt: `Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans and show which runtime agent name is active.`\n28: - Expected execution process: Grep runtime mirror folders for `deep-ai-council`, then grep for `multi-ai-council` and confirm no active primary identity remains.\n29: - Expected signals: New name appears in all four runtime mirrors; old name is absent as an active agent name.\n30: - Desired user-visible outcome: The user sees that `@deep-ai-council` is the current runtime name.\n31: - Pass/fail: PASS if all runtime mirrors expose `deep-ai-council`; FAIL if an active mirror still names `multi-ai-council`.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n(Showing lines 20-35 of 99. Use offset=36 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Objective: Verify active runtime mirrors use `deep-ai-council`.\n- Real user request: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n- Prompt: `Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans and show which runtime agent name is active.`\n- Expected execution process: Grep runtime mirror folders for `deep-ai-council`, then grep for `multi-ai-council` and confirm no active primary identity remains.\n- Expected signals: New name appears in all four runtime mirrors; old name is absent as an active agent name.\n- Desired user-visible outcome: The user sees that `@deep-ai-council` is the current runtime name.\n- Pass/fail: PASS if all runtime mirrors expose `deep-ai-council`; FAIL if an active mirror still names `multi-ai-council`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","text":"\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Objective: Verify active runtime mirrors use `deep-ai-council`.\n- Real user request: Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans.\n- Prompt: `Use the deep AI council to compare two implementation plans and show which runtime agent name is active.`\n- Expected execution process: Grep runtime mirror folders for `deep-ai-council`, then grep for `multi-ai-council` and confirm no active primary identity remains.\n- Expected signals: New name appears in all four runtime mirrors; old name is absent as an active agent name.\n- Desired user-visible outcome: The user sees that `@deep-ai-council` is the current runtime name.\n- Pass/fail: PASS if all runtime mirrors expose `deep-ai-council`; FAIL if an active mirror still names `multi-ai-council`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":35,"totalLines":99,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/01--runtime-routing-and-rename/runtime-agent-renamed-to-deep-ai-council.md","time":{"start":1782919320577,"end":1782919320585}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f3316