0\n+- Novelty: low; synthesis-focused iteration.\n+- Confidence: high for clusters A, B, C, D, F; high for E as drift, with note that E includes implementation-coupled behavior.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: deduping by contradiction class yields fixable clusters.\n+- Failed: none blocking.\n+- Ruled out: no live skill-doc stale old `deep-route-guard.js` reference found; the guard problem is README inventory omission, not lingering old name.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Patch docs in a follow-up implementation phase and decide whether the deep-improvement scanner should drop TOML mirror templates before doc wording is updated.\n","additions":34,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/014-skill-doc-drift-audit/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,93 @@\n+{\n+  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt-fast-high-1782918918795-uy16r9\",\n+  \"lineage\": \"gpt-fast-high\",\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"rq-ai-council-direct\",\n+      \"question\": \"Do docs still describe ai-council as direct/top-level after phase 010?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes. cli-opencode SKILL, README, and prompt template still teach direct or primary ai-council dispatch.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\n+        \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:31\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:285\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:76\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:386-392\",\n+        \".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/010-ai-council-subagent-only/implementation-summary.md:48-60\"\n+      ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"rq-plugin-guard\",\n+      \"question\": \"Do docs still reference the old guard or omit the renamed guard?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"No live skill docs with stale old-name references were found, but .opencode/plugins/README.md omits mk-deep-loop-guard.js and has an outdated entrypoint count.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\n+        \".opencode/plugins/README.md:1-4\",\n+        \".opencode/plugins/README.md:42-50\",\n+        \".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:1-8\"\n+      ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"rq-toml-mirrors\",\n+      \"question\": \"Do docs still require removed .opencode/agents/*.toml mirrors?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes. Core deep-loop docs, deep-ai-council SKILL, and deep-improvement scanner docs still encode TOML mirror surfaces.\",\n+      \"evidence\": [\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md:20\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md:19\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md:279-287\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:253-261\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/